victim /ˈvɪktɪm/

(victims) 

1. N-COUNT A victim is someone who has been hurt or killed. 受害者 

例： Statistically our chances of being the victims of violent crime are remote. 从统计上来看，我们成为暴力犯罪受害者的可能性是微乎其微的。 

2. N-COUNT A victim is someone who has suffered as a result of someone else's actions or beliefs, or as a result of unpleasant circumstances. 牺牲品 

例： He was a victim of racial prejudice. 他是种族偏见的一个牺牲品。 

例： He described himself and Altman as victims rather than participants in the scandal. 他把自己和奥尔特曼描述成这一丑闻的受害者，而不是参与者。

